p.del: UNITED STATES OF AMERICA Plaintiff, vs.

div1.p: In the Matter of the Application of CHIN QUOCK WAH, for a Writ of Habeas Corpus, Defendant.

Upon application of the United States Attorney, and it appearing to the Court that the above entitled cause has been concluded, and that Government's Exhibits introduced as evidence have served their purpose, it is hereby
ORDERED that the said exhibits may be withdrawn from the custody of the clerk of the court for delivery to the United States Attorney.
DONE in open court this 5th day of March, 1925.
